#pragma keywords Linux, Kernel, Operative System, Linus Torvalds, Open Source, drivers
#pragma description Summary of the changes and new features merged in the Linux Kernel during the 2.6.2 development

Linux 2.6.2 released February 4, 2004. [[http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/ChangeLog-2.6.2|Changelog]]

 * RAID 6 implementation [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=74ebb0066d038bb9792d76ee005de3e8f60c1085|commit]]
 * One-shot support for epoll [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=edd011045dadc70d9c389040f750896ee9f12630|commit]]
 * Schedulers interactivity improvements [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=8c6f4906c0e0b0229967551a9ddafd8685f1c563|commit]]
 * selinux: Add resource limit control [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=d99684fd3be9ccd3820bb72bb040294ac035e68b|commit]]
 * selinux: add netif controls [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=db5325b1fe3726083f6f5c2ed5bc9009e5e6118a|commit]]
 * selinux: Add node controls [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=85941b90bd308e89217f1b601dc9e048df303e70|commit]]
 * selinux: Add node_bind control [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=0129565dcb026535035409875fae2ba1bb1a8b55|commit]]
 * selinux: Add SO_PEERSEC socket option and getpeersec LSM hook [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=da6e57a2e6bd7939f610d957afacaf6a131e75ed|commit]]
 * selinux: Add SEND_MSG and RECV_MSG controls [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=06fbe36f2c4febcf498536e21ffd546c7ecf9e44|commit]]
 * Add netpoll API [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=8fb9cf8ab6c0ccb1b17b32c05dc9da3cc96ac229|commit]]
 * SCTP: Add sysctl parameters to update socket send/receive buffers [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=b7b0f33ff804ab7ee14ee6f2a4eac2023aff75ce|commit]]
 * net: Add HFSC packet scheduler [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=6e22ce74ea0666a869ce82f418ce78b5be089fb4|commit]]
 * IPV6: Allow per-device max addresses configurable via sysctl [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=c21c7b412096f85b650241a189f79bb10f1a48bd|commit]]
 * IPV6: Add MIB:ipv6RouterAdvert netlink notification [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=c272dd4672c7b0d2b20f84acb965f1b61694a601|commit]]
 * IPV6: Add notification for MIB:ipv6Prefix events [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=60872d54d963eefeb302ebeae15204e4be229c2b|commit]]
 * IPV6: Implement MIB:ipv6InterfaceTable [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=3c1ea2a57f835a46d08b20d72b2c3c8bc4e9c2a0|commit]]
 * AS io sched: new process estimation and tuning [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=7950701f2ef7c98a36a6160dafbc41d95283fa6b|commit]], [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=2d935b4d2fd692f153c83dd7219e3781032f238d|commit]]
 * input: Add a new ioctl to hiddev, which allows multiple usages to be set in a single request [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=eea3860a3795c78ee4e561e4032e36201fb3c0f0|commit]]
 * ACPI: add _PDC support [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=959a91bd16ee4d9a0abc809360b006284adad9c0|commit]]
 * USB Storage: add sysfs info attribute [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=8d4f1c82b9b563b39e16fff444148c1469d77440|commit]]
 * USB Storage: Sysfs attribute file for max_sectors [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=18cdc0b34bc5fa6f5cc8feb8e15f33d8622fe5a4|commit]]
 * XFS: Add the security extended attributes namespace [[https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/history/history.git/commit/?id=bd997c62b77d1a72ac39e8b7e3595585db342589|commit]]
